                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>Nennius of Bangor, priest of the high college, wrote "De origine Britannorum"; "De urbibus Cornubiae"; and "Cosmographia historiae mundi". [...]. Flourished under Caduanus, leader of the Britons in the year after the Incarnation 620.</translation>
